Blow the Trumpet in Sion, sound an Alarm in my holy Mountain, let all the Inhabitants of the earth tremble; what! Must all those turn Quakers? You that despise trembling, it seems you have not yet heard this Trumpet; Ioel 2.1. But in the day of the Lord this shall be witnessed, when streams and floods fall upon you, and consuming fire flames before and behind you; then shall
all faces gather blackness, and the earth shall quake, and the Heavens shall be moved; and this we witness, the fearful and horrible day of the Lord is upon you that despise trembling at the Word of God: when the Lord is a defence unto his people, the Heavens and the Earth shall quake, and you shall know the Lord dwels in his holy Mountain, and the Lord treadeth upon the high places of the earth; his Name is The Lord of Hosts. Ioel 4.13. Amos 8. Shall not that Land tremble that have sold the Chaff for the Corn, saith the Lord of Hosts? And shal not destruction come upon them that have seduced the people, by saying Peace, and there is no Peace? And shall not their Songs be turned into howling, and they hunger after the Word of God, and cannot find it; and the time shall come that ye shall tremble, Mic. 7. Micah 7. the Mountains tremble and quake at the Lord, Ier. 4.24. and the hills do melt at the Lord, Nahum 1.5. Nahum 1.5. these here, you see became Quakers;
Joel 2.10. they are called Mountains and Hills that be above the people, and the Mountains and the Earth shall quake, yea the whole world, and all that dwell therein; and you must be an astonishment, and stript, that you may hear this, whose knees shall t • emble then, ye that scorn quaking: The Seed is the end of the Law, Nehem. 3. and all figures and parables which pertain to the first earthly Adam, which Christ the Seed ends in, the Earth trembles, and the Heavens rend, and the Clouds drop with water. Iudges 5.

David said when his cry entered into the ears of the Lord, the earth trembled and quaked,2 Sam. 22.7, 8. Psal. 18.6, 7. Deut. 2.25. and the foundations shook, and dread and feare came upon the Nations under the whole heaven: Thou didst, O Lord, cause thy Judgements to be heard from Heaven, Psal. 77.18. Psal. 97.4. and the earth trembled and was stil; at the Voice of the Lord
there was Thunderings;
Psal. 104.32. and Lightnings, the earth shoke, & the earth trembleth at the look of the Lord, & if he touch the hills, they smoke, the earth trembled at the presence of the Lord, who carries his Lambs in his Arm, Psal. 121. Psa. 121. Thou puttest away all the ungodly from off the earth like dross; I love thy testimonie, Psal. 119.119, 120. Psal. 119.119, 121. My flesh trembleth for fear of thee, I love thy testimonie: Here you may see David was a Quaker, who loved the testimony of God, and the Word of God in his heart, and had outstript his Teachers; the earth trembled for the fear that was sent out from God, 1 Sam. 14.1 Sam. 14. you shall know this feare, though you be out of it now.
